status: MARC21-007: Color of the electronic resource
Whether the item is one color or multicolored.

definition (en): Images are intended to be produced in a single color other than black (e.g. pink and white, brown and white).
Images are intended to be produced in black and white.
Image is printed or executed in more than one color.
Image is produced with degrees of dark to light from black to gray to white.
A combination of one color, black-and-white, multicolored, hand colored, and/or other images.
Color is not applicable to the electronic resource, usually because it does not involve anything visual
Color characteristics of an item are not known.
Color other than one color, black-and-white, multicolored, gray scale, mixed.
